The Department of Water and Sanitation says that although levels are satisfactory at the moment, it does not mean the drought is over. JOHANNESBURG - The Department of Water and Sanitation says levels at the Vaal Dam have risen due to recent rainfall in Gauteng.The department has been able to stop water usage from the Sterkfontein Dam.LISTEN: Water Dept implements countrywide water restrictionsSpokesperson Sputnik Ratau says that although levels are satisfactory at the moment, it does not mean the drought is over. We are happy with what we have now, but we re aware the situation doesn t mean the drought has ended. The South African Weather Service says rainy weather can be expected throughout the week in the province.WATCH: Facing a dry future: How bad is the water crisis really?(Edited by Shimoney Regter)